text.tspan: Threshold income for each decile (before tax), United States
This is the level of income or consumption per year below which 10%, 20%, 30%, etc. of the population falls. Income
here is measured before taxes and benefits.
Note: This data is measured in international-$ at 2022 prices to account for inflation and differences in the cost of living between countries. Income
is measured before payment of taxes and non-pension benefits, but after the payment of public and private pensions.
